13. Policy Recommendations

13.1 Moratorium on Casual Universal Negation

No individual, institution, or panel shall be permitted to state “unicorns do not exist” without first filing a Form UN-0, certifying either exhaustive search completion or full universal mastery.

13.2 Burden Disclosure Requirement

All grand claims must include a burden note indicating the scale of observation required to disprove them. Statements lacking such notes shall be classified as rhetorically oversized.

13.3 Cosmological Substitution Transparency

Where unseen total explanations are invoked, speakers must acknowledge that alternative unseen total explanations may be comparably difficult to eliminate once admitted at universal scope.

13.4 Public Education

Citizens should be informed that “unlikely,” “unsupported,” and “not proven” are not equivalent to “impossible.” This will reduce preventable certainty and improve national argument hygiene.

